  <span id="freeText7889694854428325552" style="display:none">This was John Grisham' s very first book.He dreamed of getting it published,and went through innumerable rejections.It was largely ignored,when it was first published.Grisham was inspired by an actual court room case to write it.<br /><br />It is about rape,retribution and racial violence,in the American South.A young black girl is raped,and her outraged father takes justice into his own hands.A young defence attorney tries to save his life,only to find himself in danger.And then comes all that racial violence,which resembles what has been happening recently in the US.<br /><br />It is a first book,and it rambles.<br />At over 500 pages,it is too lengthy.This story could have been told so much better in half the number of pages,or even less.</span>
